.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.SS setup
.PP
.I Set up LamBoot integration for one VM (one\-time, idempotent)
.PP
.B Category:
VM Integration
.br
.B Maturity:
beta
.PP
.B SYNTAX
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
lamboot\-pve\-setup setup VMID [\-\-role ROLE] [\-\-fleet\-id ID] [\-\-running\-ok] [\-\-bios\-override]
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B ARGUMENTS
.PP
.RS 4
.TP
.B VMID
Proxmox VMID
.TP
.B \-\-role ROLE
Override role (default: from fleet.toml or Proxmox tags)
.TP
.B \-\-fleet\-id ID
Override fleet ID (default: from fleet.toml)
.TP
.B \-\-hookscript PATH
Override hookscript location
.TP
.B \-\-running\-ok
Proceed even on running VMs (changes take effect next boot)
.TP
.B \-\-bios\-override
Set up even on non\-OVMF VMs (not recommended)
.RE
.PP
.B EXAMPLES
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
sudo lamboot\-pve\-setup setup 100
sudo lamboot\-pve\-setup setup 100 \-\-role webserver \-\-fleet\-id prod\-01
sudo lamboot\-pve\-setup setup 100 \-\-dry\-run
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B NOTES
.PP
.RS 4
Idempotent: re\-running is a no\-op if already set up. Appends to existing args (never overwrites). Writes /var/lib/lamboot/<VMID>.json with initial state. Requires rewritten hookscript (lamboot\-dev >= 0.8.4) installed on host.
.RE
.PP
.B OFFLINE:
No \- requires online system
.br
.B PRIVILEGE:
Requires root (sudo)
.PP
.B SEE ALSO
.PP
.RS 4
teardown, check, doctor\-hookscript, lamboot\-pve\-fleet
.RE
.PP
.B DOCUMENTATION URL
.PP
.RS 4
.UR https://lamboot.dev/tools/pve-setup/setup
.UE
.RE
.PP
